{"article_id":"Os3f8zezsc48u31y","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"CHICAGO -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Chicago teachers uncomfortable with a tentative contract offer decided Sunday to remain on strike ,","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"insisting","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"they first wanted to consult with their full membership","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"before deciding whether to end an acrimonious standoff with Mayor Rahm Emanuel","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"that will keep 350,000 students out of class for at least two more days .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"Emanuel fired back Sunday night","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"by instructing city attorneys to seek a court order","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"forcing Chicago Teachers Union members back into the classroom .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"\" This was a strike of choice","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"and is now a delay of choice","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"that is wrong for our children , \"","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"he said in a statement .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"Meeting a week after the start of the city ' s first teachers strike in 25 years ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"the union ' s 800-member House of Delegates didn ' t hold a planned formal vote","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"on whether to suspend the strike .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"They had received a summary of a proposed settlement","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"worked out over the weekend with officials from the nation ' s third largest school district .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"Presented with a choice","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"on whether to ask members to vote on a contract","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"that union president Karen Lewis had at one point called \" a fight for the very soul of public education , \"","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"the union ' s members told their leaders","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"they needed more time","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"to talk to the rank and file .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"The contract would base teacher evaluations in part on how well students succeed and whether laid-off teachers would have first chance at open jobs in the district .","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"The union will meet again Tuesday , after the end of the Rosh Hashana , the Jewish new year .","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"\" We felt more comfortable being able to take back what ' s on the table","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"and let our constituents look at it","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"and digest it , \"","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"said Dean Refakes , a physical education teacher at Gompers Elementary School .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"\" We can have a much better decision come Tuesday . \"","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"That timeline , however , means","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"the soonest","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"classes could resume","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"would be Wednesday .","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"That frustrated both Emanuel and some parents ,","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"who learned late at night a week ago Sunday","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"that a flurry of last-minute negotiations had failed to produce a contract agreement","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"and that the strike was on .","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"\" I think","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"a week is a long time","depth":13},{"id":41,"text":"to be wasting time .","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"Another week would be murder .","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"I don ' t think","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"it ' s right , \"","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"said Beatriz Fierro , the mother of a fifth grader .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"\" They should be back in school .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"I don ' t think","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"teachers should be on strike that long . \"","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"Other parents continued to stand with the teachers .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"As teachers walked picket lines in the past week","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"and rallied Saturday in a park near downtown ,","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"they were joined by parents","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"who have had to scramble","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"to find baby sitters or a supervised place","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"for children","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"to pass the time .","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"\" As much as we want our kids back in school ,","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"teachers need to make sure","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"they have dotted all their I ' s and crossed their T ' s , \"","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"said Becky Malone , mother of a second grader and fourth grader .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"\" What ' s the point","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"of going on strike","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"if you don ' t get everything","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"you need out of it ?","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"For parents , it ' ll be no more of a challenge","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"than it ' s been in the past week . \"","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"Emanuel didn ' t appear at a brief news conference Sunday night with city school board president David Vitale ,","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"who said","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"147 schools","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"staffed with non-union workers and central office employees","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"would be open Monday for students","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"who are dependent on school-provided meals .","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"But in a statement , Emanuel was typically blunt .","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"He accused the union of using the city ' s students as \" pawns in an internal dispute. \"","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"He said","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"the strike was illegal","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"because it endangers the health and safety of students","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"and concerned issues","depth":14},{"id":79,"text":"that","depth":16},{"id":80,"text":"state law says","depth":16},{"id":81,"text":"can not be grounds for a work stoppage .","depth":15},{"id":82,"text":"\" While the union works through its remaining issues ,","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"there is no reason","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"why the children of Chicago should not be back in the classroom","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"as they had been for weeks","depth":15},{"id":86,"text":"while negotiators worked through these same issues , \"","depth":15},{"id":87,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"Emanuel believes","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"the strike is illegal","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"because state law bars teachers from walking out over evaluations and layoffs and recall ,","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"spokeswoman Sarah Hamilton said .","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"Lewis has said","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"the strike was not mainly about money .","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"But union delegate Susan Hickey , a school social worker , said","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"many also were upset","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"that a 4 percent pay raise","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"rescinded by Emanuel last year","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"was not addressed in the proposed deal","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"and weren ' t happy with some changes to health benefits .","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"Even so , Hickey said","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"she believes","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"the proposed contract is one","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"that teachers still could support .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"She said","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"she and other teachers are worried","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"that","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"if the strike goes beyond mid-week ,","depth":14},{"id":108,"text":"they will risk the wrath of parents .","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"\" Personally I think","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"there ' s a lot of us","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"who don ' t want to lose the parental support , \"","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"she said .","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"The walkout , the first for a major American city in at least six years , canceled classes for students","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"who just returned from summer vacation","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"and forced tens of thousands of parents to find alternatives for idle children ,","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"including many","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"whose neighborhoods have been wracked by gang violence in recent months .","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"With an average salary of $ 76,000 , Chicago teachers are among the highest-paid in the nation .","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"The contract outline calls for annual raises ,","depth":6},{"id":120,"text":"but it doesn ' t restore a 4 percent raise","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"that was rescinded by the mayor last year .","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"Lewis said","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"delegates weren ' t willing to go back to the classroom","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"while contract language was amended","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"because of the level of distrust between the union and the city , and the fact","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"the settlement on the table remains tentative .","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"\" The trust level is just not there , \"","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"Lewis said .","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"\" You have a population of people","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"who are frightened of never being able to work for no fault of their own .","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"They just don ' t have the trust . \"","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"Emanuel ,","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"who did not personally negotiate the deal","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"but monitored the talks through aides ,","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"has pushed hard for a contract","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"that includes ratcheting up the percentage of evaluations","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"based on student performance ,","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"to 35 percent within four years .","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"The union contends","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"that is unfair","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"because it does not take into account outside factors","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"that affect student performance such as poverty , violence and homelessness .","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"The union also pushed for a policy","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"to give laid-off teachers first dibs on open jobs anywhere in the district ,","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"which","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"the city said","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"that would keep principals from hiring the teachers","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"they thought best qualified for the position .","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"\" They ' re still not happy with the evaluation ( s ) , \"","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"Lewis said .","depth":9},{"id":151,"text":"\" They ' re not happy with the recall .","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"They don ' t like the idea","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"that people ' s recall benefits are cut in half . \"","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"The teachers walked out Sept. 10 after months of tense contract talks","depth":7},{"id":155,"text":"that for a time appeared to be headed toward a peaceful resolution .","depth":7},{"id":156,"text":"Emanuel and the union agreed in July on a deal","depth":7},{"id":157,"text":"to implement a longer school day with a plan","depth":9},{"id":158,"text":"to hire back 477 teachers","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"who had been laid off","depth":10},{"id":160,"text":"rather than pay regular teachers more","depth":9},{"id":161,"text":"to work longer hours .","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"That raised hopes","depth":7},{"id":163,"text":"the contract would be settled before the start of fall classes ,","depth":8},{"id":164,"text":"but bargaining stalled on other issues .","depth":8},{"id":165,"text":"To win friends ,","depth":7},{"id":166,"text":"the union","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"representing 25,500 teachers ,","depth":10},{"id":168,"text":"engaged in something of a publicity campaign ,","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"telling parents repeatedly about problems with schools and the barriers","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"that have made it more difficult to serve their kids .","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"They described classrooms","depth":11},{"id":172,"text":"that are stifling hot","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"without air conditioning ,","depth":12},{"id":174,"text":"important books","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"that are unavailable","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"and supplies as basic as toilet paper","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"that are sometimes in short supply .","depth":12},{"id":178,"text":"The strike upended a district","depth":8},{"id":179,"text":"in which the vast majority of students are poor and minority .","depth":8},{"id":180,"text":"It also raised the concerns of parents","depth":8},{"id":181,"text":"who worried not just about their kids ' education but their safety .","depth":8},{"id":182,"text":"Chicago ' s gang violence has spiked this year ,","depth":7},{"id":183,"text":"with scores of shootings reported throughout the summer","depth":8},{"id":184,"text":"and bystanders sometimes caught in the crossfire .","depth":8},{"id":185,"text":"\" I don ' t like being on strike .","depth":7},{"id":186,"text":"Nobody in my school likes being on strike ,","depth":10},{"id":187,"text":"but we understand the reason .","depth":11},{"id":188,"text":"It ' s not an easy process , \"","depth":11},{"id":189,"text":"said Michael Bochner , a teacher at Cesar Chavez Elementary .","depth":9},{"id":190,"text":"\" My membership ,","depth":10},{"id":191,"text":"\"","depth":11},{"id":192,"text":"he said ,","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"\" really wants to go back to work . \"","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":387,"left":0,"right":386,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":386,"left":259,"right":385,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":259,"left":205,"right":258,"relation":"elaboration","nuc